text: In the Execute view, if the whole epic is done, show a green checkmark to the left of the epic's name

proposedTasks.title: Show green checkmark on completed epics in Execute view
proposedTasks.description: In the Execute tab's epic card list, display a green checkmark icon to the left of the epic's name when all child tasks under that epic have status Done. Acceptance criteria: (1) A green checkmark icon appears immediately to the left of the epic title when every child task is Done. (2) The checkmark is not shown when any child task is in a non-Done state (Planning, Backlog, Ready, In Progress, In Review, Blocked). (3) The icon updates in real-time via WebSocket state changes without requiring a page refresh. (4) The checkmark uses the existing theme's success/green color token for light and dark mode consistency.

taskTitles: Show green checkmark on completed epics in Execute view
